				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great list! &#8211; thanks. I second Mr. Shattuck&#8217;s nominations of Fred Anderson&#8217;s great books, and would add his The War That Made America (which is a condensed version of Crucible of War). I also want to mention the book that got me &#8220;hooked&#8221; on American Revolution history at age ten: The American Heritage Book of the Revolution by Bruce Lancaster (used hardcover copies sell for $5.99 via amazon).</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

