					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2017/03/100-best-american-revolution-books-time/#comment-99511"><time datetime="2017-03-10T15:44:56-05:00">March 10, 2017 at 3:44 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Great points, Richard.  And I thoroughly endorse your reference to Elkins and McKittrick.</p>
<p>You are also on point with looking forward as well as backwards from the Rev War itself.  In historical archaeology, the perspective you refer to is called &#8220;bi-directional temporization&#8221; &#8211; in other words, the rejection of &#8220;periodization,&#8221; or, the focus on the immediate.  Context is everything and events taking place both before and after the war are crucial to gaining a full understanding.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-99511' data-commentid="99511" data-postid="13549" data-belowelement="div-comment-99511" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Gary Shattuck" aria-label='Reply to Gary Shattuck'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
