				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>I cannot recommend Robert Gross&#8217; &#8220;The Minutemen and Their World&#8221; enough. Captures the time and the crisis exceedingly well. Every page seems to shed light on a new facet that led to the outbreak of the war. Good to see it listed here. I also highly recommend David Hackett Fischer&#8217;s &#8220;Paul Revere&#8217;s Ride,&#8221; also listed here.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

