									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>&#8220;The Fate of a Nation The American Revolution through contemporary eyes&#8221; by William P. Cumming and Hugh Rankin, is a combination of first person accounts and illustrations from the era. Published in 1975, hardcover copies are available from Alibris and Amazon starting at $2.96. The book is 352 pages in length.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

