				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Not sure how Charles Royster&#8217;s A Revolutionary People at War didn&#8217;t make the list.  It&#8217;s a superlative combination of the social and economic with military history. Readable and solid on every topic.<br />
I&#8217;ll second the nomination of John Shy&#8217;s A People Numerous and Armed.</p>
