				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>The lovely reality of publishing in the 21st century is that old, even out of print, doesn&#8217;t mean searching for Royster, Shy or Gruber in the backs of used bookstores and estate sales, hoping to get lucky. All are available on Amazon, perhaps even on other on-line outlets. </p>
<p>Perhaps a list of solid, timeless classics, or a &#8216;grab it if you find it&#8217; list? </p>
<p>Thanks for this, absolutely, thanks &#8211; it&#8217;s a handy, reliable list for reference or referrals.</p>
