					<p>I&#8217;m surprised you think American Sphinx is the best book on Thomas Jefferson. I wonder how many (or how few) Jefferson scholars would agree. Ellis is a fine writer, but even his title suggests he doesn&#8217;t really understand Jefferson. What about Dumas Malone and Merrill Peterson?</p>
