			<article id="div-comment-99738" class="comment-body">
				<footer class="comment-meta">
					<div class="comment-author vcard">
						<img alt='' src='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/03581731527732cc8331280e8cae046d?s=32&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g' srcset='https://secure.gravatar.com/avatar/03581731527732cc8331280e8cae046d?s=64&#038;d=mm&#038;r=g 2x' class='avatar avatar-32 photo' height='32' width='32' loading='lazy' decoding='async'/>						<b class="fn">Eastjersey Steve</b> <span class="says">says:</span>					</div><!-- .comment-author -->

					<div class="comment-metadata">
						<a href="https://allthingsliberty.com/2017/03/100-best-american-revolution-books-time/#comment-99738"><time datetime="2017-03-13T16:50:18-04:00">March 13, 2017 at 4:50 pm</time></a>					</div><!-- .comment-metadata -->

									</footer><!-- .comment-meta -->

				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>Interesting list, I think articles like these are more useful for the conversations they create than an actual status as a &#8220;definitive&#8221; list.  That said, I feel there are a few books that warrant mentioning:</p>
<p>Mark Lender and James Martin&#8217;s &#8220;A Respectable Army&#8221; is a great short volume that provides a clear, concise, academic overview of the war, and its extensive bibliographic essay is truly a definitive list of relevant scholarship.  </p>
<p>The social history of the Continental Army has been a major focus of historians in recent decades.  Works such as Charles Neimeyer, &#8220;America Goes to War,&#8221; Caroline Cox, &#8220;A Proper Sense of Honor;&#8221; or Holly Mayer, &#8220;Belonging to the Army;&#8221; are all important works.  Also, works on war and society, such as Judith van Buskirk, &#8220;Generous Enemies;&#8221; Sylvia R. Frey &#8220;Water From a Rock;&#8221; or Wayne Bodle &#8220;The Valley Forge Winter,&#8221; are also great works in their subfield.  </p>
<p>Curiously, there are very few books about women, or by women on the list.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

				<div class="reply"><a rel='nofollow' class='comment-reply-link' href='#comment-99738' data-commentid="99738" data-postid="13549" data-belowelement="div-comment-99738" data-respondelement="respond" data-replyto="Reply to Eastjersey Steve" aria-label='Reply to Eastjersey Steve'>Reply</a></div>			</article><!-- .comment-body -->
