					<p>I am surprised there is no The War of the Revolution by Christopher Ward? Published 1952. The Two Volumes is indispensable and unsurpassed single volume on the war.  Omitting this book is like omitting David M. Glantz in the conversation about best books on Stalingrad.</p>
