				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>&#8220;Pictorial Field Book of the Revolution&#8221; by B. J. Lossing?   Lossing traveled the country before the Civil War talking to surviving participants and their close descendants and neighbors, reading their handwritten materials, and drawing scenes to engrave for the book.  (He did the same for the War of 1812 and the Civil War.)  Preserves a fair bit of original source material, and gives a non-modern perspective.</p>
