				<div class="comment-content">
					<p>A great list! For my contributions, two worthy candidates would be &#8220;The Long Fuse: How England Lost the American Colonies 1760-1785&#8221; by Don Cook and &#8220;King George III and the Politicians&#8221; by Richard Pares. Both books really get into the mechanisms behind Parliament&#8217;s plotting and planning, and Cook spends time unraveling the motives behind Benjamin Franklin&#8217;s turn from wannabe-Parliamentarian to staunch American Patriot that really drives home how vital his involvement was to achieving our lasting independence.</p>
				</div><!-- .comment-content -->

